ratings.comment: Gabe is honestly one of the best teachers I've ever had at SBCC. He teaches the material very clearly and evens out your grade so that everything makes sense in the end. I got an A in his 107 class and the statistics class as well. He teaches you how to go through each problem with all of his clear steps. WOULD RECOMMEND!!

Explains everything extremely succinctly and clearly. Hard subject matter, but with a little effort it's an easy class. Tests are reasonable (check your work) and he gives partial credit. He's a really nice teacher and is always willing to help. He also gives out practice problems that are really helpful, maybe more than the homework.

Provides notes and handouts and exam reviews and lists book homework. I think he attended twice his expected office hours because he felt there was demand for it.  The exams I felt were a good representation of the assigned workload. I think he'd probably never put something on an exam that he didn't cover twice in class. I'd recommend him.

Best TA ever. Math 222 was a nightmare, but when I took WES with him, I fell in love with Calculus. He is phenomenal. Works his butt off so that you understand his discussion sections. I can't put it any other way - he should be teaching lecture, he's better than the professor.
Gabriel is definitely the best TA I've had at UW. He breaks the material down into what you need to know.
Awesome TA, best I've had in the math department. He has lots of office hours and is always willing to explain a concept to you, and unlike most TA's he's actually good at explaining them.
